/* Read Training data using spark-csv */

val df = sqlContext.read
    .format("com.databricks.spark.csv")
    .option("header", "true") // Use first line of all files as header
    .option("inferSchema", "true") // Automatically infer data types //.option("quote", "\"")
    .option("mode", "DROPMALFORMED")
    .load("file:///Users/vaishalilambe/Downloads/train_ver2.csv")

/*dataframe as table */    
df.registerTempTable("sbank")

/* print columns of the dataframe */
df.columns.map(c => println(c))

/* Finding distrubution of gender */
%spark.sql
select count(sexo), 
       sexo as Gender
from sbank
--where sexo IS NOT NULL
group by sexo

/* Counting number of cutomers having same last date as primary customer */
%spark.sql
select count(ult_fec_cli_1t), ult_fec_cli_1t as Last_Date
from sbank
group by ult_fec_cli_1t
order by ult_fec_cli_1t asc

/* Distribution of customer identification as VIP, Individuals or students*/
%spark.sql
select count(segmento), segmento as Cust_Identification 
from sbank
group by segmento

/* Distribution of customer Type */
%spark.sql
select count(indrel),indrel as Cust_Type
from sbank
group by indrel

/* Average gross income for each type of customer identification */
%spark.sql
select avg(renta) as Avg_Gross_Income, segmento as Cust_Identification 
from sbank
where segmento is NOT NULL
group by segmento

/* Average gross income for each gener type */
%spark.sql
select avg(renta) as Avg_Gross_Income, sexo as Gender
from sbank
where sexo IS NOT NULL
group by sexo

/* Districution for gender and customer identification */
%spark.sql
select count(sexo) as Count_Gender, count(segmento) as Count_Cust_Identification, sexo as Gender, segmento as Cust_Identification
from sbank
where sexo IS NOT NULL
and segmento IS NOT NULL
group by sexo,segmento

/* Read Training data using spark-csv */
%spark.sql
select count(ind_ahor_fin_ult1) as Num_Saving_Acc, count(ind_cco_fin_ult1) as Num_Guarantees, count(ind_cco_fin_ult1) as Num_Current_Accounts,count(ind_cder_fin_ult1) as Num_Derivada_Account,count(sexo) as Num_Gender, sexo as Gender, count(segmento) as Num_Cust_Identification, segmento as Cust_Identification,avg(renta) as Avg_Gross_Income
from sbank
where ind_ahor_fin_ult1 is NOT NULL
and renta is NOT NULL
and sexo is NOT NULL
and segmento is NOT NULL
group by ind_ahor_fin_ult1,sexo,segmento

%spark.sql
select count(ind_cno_fin_ult1) as Num_Payroll_Acc, count(ind_ctju_fin_ult1) as Num_Junior_Acc, count(ind_ctma_fin_ult1) as Num_Mas_Acc,count(ind_ctop_fin_ult1) as Num_Perticular_Acc,count(sexo) as Num_Gender, sexo as Gender, count(segmento) as Num_Cust_Identification, segmento as Cust_Identification,avg(renta) as Avg_Gross_Income
from sbank
where ind_ahor_fin_ult1 is NOT NULL
and renta is NOT NULL
and sexo is NOT NULL
and segmento is NOT NULL
group by ind_ahor_fin_ult1,sexo,segmento

/* Ditribution of few products across gender, customer identification, avg gross income */
%spark.sql
select count(ind_ctpp_fin_ult1) as Num_Perticular_Plus_Acc, count(ind_deco_fin_ult1) as Num_Short_Term_Deposit, count(ind_deme_fin_ult1) as Num_Medium_Term_Deposit,count(ind_dela_fin_ult1) as Num_Long_Term_Deposit,count(sexo) as Num_Gender, sexo as Gender, count(segmento) as Num_Cust_Identification, segmento as Cust_Identification,avg(renta) as Avg_Gross_Income
from sbank
where ind_ahor_fin_ult1 is NOT NULL
and renta is NOT NULL
and sexo is NOT NULL
and segmento is NOT NULL
group by ind_ahor_fin_ult1,sexo,segmento

/* Ditribution of few products across gender, customer identification, avg gross income */
%spark.sql
select count(ind_ecue_fin_ult1) as Num_e_Acc, count(ind_fond_fin_ult1) as Num_Funds, count(ind_hip_fin_ult1) as Num_Mortgage,count(ind_plan_fin_ult1) as Num_Pensions,count(sexo) as Num_Gender, sexo as Gender, count(segmento) as Num_Cust_Identification, segmento as Cust_Identification,avg(renta) as Avg_Gross_Income
from sbank
where ind_ahor_fin_ult1 is NOT NULL
and renta is NOT NULL
and sexo is NOT NULL
and segmento is NOT NULL
group by ind_ahor_fin_ult1,sexo,segmento

%spark.sql
select count(ind_pres_fin_ult1) as Num_Loans, count(ind_reca_fin_ult1) as Num_Taxes, count(ind_tjcr_fin_ult1) as Num_Credit_Cards,count(ind_plan_fin_ult1) as Num_Securities,count(sexo) as Num_Gender, sexo as Gender, count(segmento) as Num_Cust_Identification, segmento as Cust_Identification,avg(renta) as Avg_Gross_Income
from sbank
where ind_ahor_fin_ult1 is NOT NULL
and renta is NOT NULL
and sexo is NOT NULL
and segmento is NOT NULL
group by ind_ahor_fin_ult1,sexo,segmento
